{"id": "EUVD-2025-20799", "enisaUuid": "f17c511e-20c2-3e38-b069-603e61dce742", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ntty: serial: uartlite: register uart driver in init\n\nWhen two instances of uart devices are probing, a concurrency race can\noccur. If one thread calls uart_register_driver function, which first\nallocates and assigns memory to 'uart_state' member of uart_driver\nstructure, the other instance can bypass uart driver registration and\ncall ulite_assign. This calls uart_add_one_port, which expects the uart\ndriver to be fully initialized. This leads to a kernel panic due to a\nnull pointer dereference:\n\n[    8.143581] BUG: kernel NULL pointer dereference, address: 00000000000002b8\n[    8.156982] #PF: supervisor write access in kernel mode\n[    8.156984] #PF: error_code(0x0002) - not-present page\n[    8.156986] PGD 0 P4D 0\n...\n[    8.180668] RIP: 0010:mutex_lock+0x19/0x30\n[    8.188624] Call Trace:\n[    8.188629]  ? __die_body.cold+0x1a/0x1f\n[    8.195260]  ? page_fault_oops+0x15c/0x290\n[    8.209183]  ? __irq_resolve_mapping+0x47/0x80\n[    8.209187]  ? exc_page_fault+0x64/0x140\n[    8.209190]  ? asm_exc_page_fault+0x22/0x30\n[    8.209196]  ? mutex_lock+0x19/0x30\n[    8.223116]  uart_add_one_port+0x60/0x440\n[    8.223122]  ? proc_tty_register_driver+0x43/0x50\n[    8.223126]  ? tty_register_driver+0x1ca/0x1e0\n[    8.246250]  ulite_probe+0x357/0x4b0 [uartlite]\n\nTo prevent it, move uart driver registration in to init function. This\nwill ensure that uart_driver is always registered when probe function\nis called.", "datePublished": "2025-07-09T12:31:35", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-18T18:30:28", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6db06aaea07bb7c8e33a425cf7b98bf29ee6056e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8e958d10dd0ce5ae674cce460db5c9ca3f25243b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/685d29f2c5057b32c7b1b46f2a7d303b926c8f72", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f5e4229d94792b40e750f30c92bcf7a3107c72ef", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6bd697b5fc39fd24e2aa418c7b7d14469f550a93", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9c905fdbba68a6d73d39a6b7de9b9f0d6c46df87", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5015eed450005bab6e5cb6810f7a62eab0434fc4", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38262", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/10/msg00008.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38262"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "06a35836-fc49-3b42-9eb6-6a75a3ca2ad1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <f5e4229d94792b40e750f30c92bcf7a3107c72ef"}, {"id": "0af19727-39ba-383f-a0fe-3a308de05355", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.4.296"}, {"id": "0c584cb6-5400-3aea-97a0-7dbd899de3ea", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "238b8721a554a33a451a3f13bdb5be8fe5cfc927 <9c905fdbba68a6d73d39a6b7de9b9f0d6c46df87"}, {"id": "0f933aeb-94ca-3b8e-8317-ecd23f925666", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <6db06aaea07bb7c8e33a425cf7b98bf29ee6056e"}, {"id": "14ae3f3e-6ee4-3ddb-9ddf-f08b405f71a6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <8e958d10dd0ce5ae674cce460db5c9ca3f25243b"}, {"id": "1f0de0c6-095f-3ed3-965d-0ec9fbe4fd35", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.5"}, {"id": "48614962-8f84-384b-a3af-7bd1976549bb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <9c905fdbba68a6d73d39a6b7de9b9f0d6c46df87"}, {"id": "57c6fbb1-22a3-3eda-83f6-07a212d3684c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "238b8721a554a33a451a3f13bdb5be8fe5cfc927 <8e958d10dd0ce5ae674cce460db5c9ca3f25243b"}, {"id": "65fb131c-3667-3941-a93c-5c95ecac971d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "238b8721a554a33a451a3f13bdb5be8fe5cfc927 <685d29f2c5057b32c7b1b46f2a7d303b926c8f72"}, {"id": "6a74ba15-051